Dialogue: 0,0:00:20.18,0:00:20.62,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Good morning.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:21.30,0:00:22.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you all for coming.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:23.09,0:00:24.21,Default,,0,0,0,,My name is Ian Parks.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:25.66,0:00:25.95,Default,,0,0,0,,[Applause] Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:26.52,0:00:28.57,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Applause ]
Dialogue: 0,0:00:29.07,0:00:30.22,Default,,0,0,0,,My name is Ian Parks and I work
Dialogue: 0,0:00:30.22,0:00:31.46,Default,,0,0,0,,on the watchOS software team.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:32.08,0:00:33.27,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm really excited to tell you
Dialogue: 0,0:00:33.27,0:00:35.42,Default,,0,0,0,,what's new in watchOS 4 and what
Dialogue: 0,0:00:35.42,0:00:37.09,Default,,0,0,0,,that's going to mean for you as
Dialogue: 0,0:00:37.09,0:00:38.92,Default,,0,0,0,,developers so you can continue
Dialogue: 0,0:00:38.92,0:00:40.67,Default,,0,0,0,,to deliver fantastic apps on
Dialogue: 0,0:00:40.67,0:00:41.35,Default,,0,0,0,,watchOS.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:41.88,0:00:43.43,Default,,0,0,0,,It's only been two years since
Dialogue: 0,0:00:43.43,0:00:44.89,Default,,0,0,0,,we first released Apple Watch
Dialogue: 0,0:00:45.26,0:00:46.52,Default,,0,0,0,,and the platform has come a long
Dialogue: 0,0:00:46.52,0:00:46.77,Default,,0,0,0,,way.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:47.64,0:00:48.80,Default,,0,0,0,,We're continuing to learn from
Dialogue: 0,0:00:48.80,0:00:50.88,Default,,0,0,0,,our users and how Apple Watch is
Dialogue: 0,0:00:50.88,0:00:52.12,Default,,0,0,0,,continuing to make a difference
Dialogue: 0,0:00:52.12,0:00:53.28,Default,,0,0,0,,in their lives.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:53.50,0:00:55.05,Default,,0,0,0,,And this year we're adding a ton
Dialogue: 0,0:00:55.05,0:00:56.80,Default,,0,0,0,,of new features in watchOS 4.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:56.80,0:00:59.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Like a brand new news app that
Dialogue: 0,0:00:59.89,0:01:01.50,Default,,0,0,0,,lets you browse headlines and
Dialogue: 0,0:01:01.50,0:01:02.66,Default,,0,0,0,,mark the ones you'd like to read
Dialogue: 0,0:01:02.66,0:01:03.01,Default,,0,0,0,,later.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:03.01,0:01:05.29,Default,,0,0,0,,And a totally redesigned music
Dialogue: 0,0:01:05.29,0:01:06.90,Default,,0,0,0,,experience that lets you sync
Dialogue: 0,0:01:06.90,0:01:08.96,Default,,0,0,0,,multiple playlists and it has a
Dialogue: 0,0:01:08.96,0:01:10.53,Default,,0,0,0,,new interface that's both fun
Dialogue: 0,0:01:10.53,0:01:11.50,Default,,0,0,0,,and easy to use.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:16.10,0:01:17.25,Default,,0,0,0,,We were also trying to make
Dialogue: 0,0:01:17.37,0:01:18.64,Default,,0,0,0,,workflows more efficient for
Dialogue: 0,0:01:18.64,0:01:20.93,Default,,0,0,0,,users like being able to access
Dialogue: 0,0:01:20.93,0:01:22.56,Default,,0,0,0,,to the now playing UI right from
Dialogue: 0,0:01:22.56,0:01:26.78,Default,,0,0,0,,inside of a workout as well as
Dialogue: 0,0:01:26.78,0:01:28.59,Default,,0,0,0,,surfacing important information
Dialogue: 0,0:01:28.81,0:01:31.03,Default,,0,0,0,,throughout your day in a new
Dialogue: 0,0:01:31.03,0:01:32.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Siri watch face.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:32.63,0:01:35.75,Default,,0,0,0,,And of course, we're introducing
Dialogue: 0,0:01:35.75,0:01:37.04,Default,,0,0,0,,a ton of new features for
Dialogue: 0,0:01:37.04,0:01:38.90,Default,,0,0,0,,developer so you can continue to
Dialogue: 0,0:01:38.90,0:01:40.40,Default,,0,0,0,,create great watchOS apps.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:40.92,0:01:42.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Now last year we introduced
Dialogue: 0,0:01:42.69,0:01:44.74,Default,,0,0,0,,three guiding principles for how
Dialogue: 0,0:01:44.74,0:01:45.75,Default,,0,0,0,,to create great Watch
Dialogue: 0,0:01:45.75,0:01:46.59,Default,,0,0,0,,experiences.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:47.04,0:01:48.36,Default,,0,0,0,,And we're continuing to pursue
Dialogue: 0,0:01:48.36,0:01:50.59,Default,,0,0,0,,these in our system apps as well
Dialogue: 0,0:01:50.59,0:01:51.87,Default,,0,0,0,,as how we're creating frameworks
Dialogue: 0,0:01:51.87,0:01:52.19,Default,,0,0,0,,for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:53.15,0:01:54.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's take a moment to look back
Dialogue: 0,0:01:54.73,0:01:55.85,Default,,0,0,0,,at these and see how they're
Dialogue: 0,0:01:55.85,0:01:57.47,Default,,0,0,0,,continuing to drive interactions
Dialogue: 0,0:01:57.62,0:01:58.39,Default,,0,0,0,,in watchOS.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:00.42,0:02:01.89,Default,,0,0,0,,The first is making our app
Dialogue: 0,0:02:01.99,0:02:02.57,Default,,0,0,0,,glanceable.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:03.41,0:02:04.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Interactions on Apple Watch are
Dialogue: 0,0:02:04.98,0:02:05.69,Default,,0,0,0,,very short.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:05.83,0:02:07.49,Default,,0,0,0,,And the screen size is much
Dialogue: 0,0:02:07.49,0:02:09.00,Default,,0,0,0,,smaller than on other platforms.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:09.00,0:02:11.14,Default,,0,0,0,,So we need to carefully consider
Dialogue: 0,0:02:11.14,0:02:13.13,Default,,0,0,0,,what information to present on
Dialogue: 0,0:02:13.13,0:02:15.30,Default,,0,0,0,,the UI and make sure that it's
Dialogue: 0,0:02:15.38,0:02:16.80,Default,,0,0,0,,well designed information so the
Dialogue: 0,0:02:16.80,0:02:19.21,Default,,0,0,0,,user can quickly absorb and
Dialogue: 0,0:02:19.36,0:02:20.53,Default,,0,0,0,,respond to the information.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:27.05,0:02:28.77,Default,,0,0,0,,And the second is making the
Dialogue: 0,0:02:28.77,0:02:29.89,Default,,0,0,0,,information actionable.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:29.99,0:02:32.31,Default,,0,0,0,,And what we mean by this is
Dialogue: 0,0:02:32.34,0:02:34.24,Default,,0,0,0,,bringing pieces that the user
Dialogue: 0,0:02:34.24,0:02:36.13,Default,,0,0,0,,can respond to either within the
Dialogue: 0,0:02:36.13,0:02:37.99,Default,,0,0,0,,application like changing a
Dialogue: 0,0:02:37.99,0:02:40.15,Default,,0,0,0,,music track or sometimes in
Dialogue: 0,0:02:40.15,0:02:41.10,Default,,0,0,0,,their current surroundings.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:41.78,0:02:42.92,Default,,0,0,0,,A quick glance at weather
Dialogue: 0,0:02:42.92,0:02:44.16,Default,,0,0,0,,conditions, for example, can
Dialogue: 0,0:02:44.16,0:02:45.17,Default,,0,0,0,,tell me whether or not I need to
Dialogue: 0,0:02:45.17,0:02:46.57,Default,,0,0,0,,pick up an umbrella on my way
Dialogue: 0,0:02:46.57,0:02:48.65,Default,,0,0,0,,out the door but actionable
Dialogue: 0,0:02:48.65,0:02:50.10,Default,,0,0,0,,information can also come in the
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.10,0:02:51.23,Default,,0,0,0,,form of audio too.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.15,0:02:54.90,Default,,0,0,0,,For instance, I can get in ear
Dialogue: 0,0:02:54.90,0:02:56.44,Default,,0,0,0,,coaching during a workout to
Dialogue: 0,0:02:56.44,0:02:57.62,Default,,0,0,0,,tell me when I've fallen behind
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.62,0:02:58.18,Default,,0,0,0,,my pace.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.72,0:03:00.99,Default,,0,0,0,,And finally responsive.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.03,0:03:03.42,Default,,0,0,0,,While performance is a really
Dialogue: 0,0:03:03.42,0:03:05.20,Default,,0,0,0,,crucial metric for watchOS apps,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.71,0:03:06.87,Default,,0,0,0,,we mean a bit more when we say
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.87,0:03:07.61,Default,,0,0,0,,responsive here.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.14,0:03:09.99,Default,,0,0,0,,This also means making sure that
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.99,0:03:12.17,Default,,0,0,0,,your content remains up-to-date
Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.17,0:03:12.64,Default,,0,0,0,,always.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.64,0:03:14.15,Default,,0,0,0,,And it also takes into
Dialogue: 0,0:03:14.15,0:03:15.69,Default,,0,0,0,,consideration what the user
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.69,0:03:17.23,Default,,0,0,0,,might want to do next in your
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.23,0:03:17.82,Default,,0,0,0,,application.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.77,0:03:19.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's take a look at a few
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.77,0:03:21.16,Default,,0,0,0,,examples of how these are
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.16,0:03:22.41,Default,,0,0,0,,manifesting themselves in
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.41,0:03:22.98,Default,,0,0,0,,watchOS 4.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.25,0:03:29.56,Default,,0,0,0,,So last year, we introduced the
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.56,0:03:30.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Quick Start workout feature
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.60,0:03:33.98,Default,,0,0,0,,which let you start the workout
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.98,0:03:35.95,Default,,0,0,0,,that you most commonly do very
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.95,0:03:36.37,Default,,0,0,0,,quickly.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.93,0:03:38.42,Default,,0,0,0,,The idea being that you're most
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.42,0:03:39.64,Default,,0,0,0,,commonly going to use the same
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.64,0:03:40.67,Default,,0,0,0,,workout over and over.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.14,0:03:42.83,Default,,0,0,0,,So we let use the same goal that
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.83,0:03:44.54,Default,,0,0,0,,you've set previously to get
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.54,0:03:45.85,Default,,0,0,0,,started in just a few seconds
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.67,0:03:48.43,Default,,0,0,0,,but if you do a rotating set of
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.43,0:03:49.92,Default,,0,0,0,,workouts like do you do a run
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.92,0:03:50.47,Default,,0,0,0,,one day?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.80,0:03:52.32,Default,,0,0,0,,And you do a swim the next day
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.32,0:03:53.55,Default,,0,0,0,,and the bicycle ride the day
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.55,0:03:54.10,Default,,0,0,0,,after that?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.58,0:03:55.98,Default,,0,0,0,,First of all, congratulations
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.98,0:03:56.77,Default,,0,0,0,,because you're getting a lot of
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.77,0:03:57.45,Default,,0,0,0,,exercise.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.19,0:03:59.67,Default,,0,0,0,,But also you're going to have an
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.67,0:04:01.94,Default,,0,0,0,,extra step every time of setting
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.94,0:04:02.26,Default,,0,0,0,,a goal.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.76,0:04:05.14,Default,,0,0,0,,So in watchOS 4, we've made this
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.14,0:04:05.84,Default,,0,0,0,,a lot easier.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.51,0:04:07.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Every workout will track the
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.94,0:04:09.75,Default,,0,0,0,,previous goal that you've set
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.75,0:04:11.85,Default,,0,0,0,,for that workout type and if you
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.85,0:04:13.41,Default,,0,0,0,,haven't set one, with defaults
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.41,0:04:14.19,Default,,0,0,0,,to an open goal.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.66,0:04:15.70,Default,,0,0,0,,And that means that every
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.70,0:04:17.13,Default,,0,0,0,,workout type is a Quick Start
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.13,0:04:17.48,Default,,0,0,0,,workout.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.30,0:04:19.60,Default,,0,0,0,,This is a great example of
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.60,0:04:21.20,Default,,0,0,0,,making the most common action
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.20,0:04:22.33,Default,,0,0,0,,that the user's going to take
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.55,0:04:23.95,Default,,0,0,0,,the easiest one for them.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.27,0:04:26.45,Default,,0,0,0,,It lets them glance at the UI
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.45,0:04:28.29,Default,,0,0,0,,and get started very quickly.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.87,0:04:31.28,Default,,0,0,0,,And while you're inside of a
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.28,0:04:33.03,Default,,0,0,0,,workout, you can now add a
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.03,0:04:34.22,Default,,0,0,0,,second workout into your
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.22,0:04:34.66,Default,,0,0,0,,routine.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.11,0:04:36.32,Default,,0,0,0,,For example, if I wanted to
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.32,0:04:37.67,Default,,0,0,0,,start with a high intensity
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.67,0:04:39.60,Default,,0,0,0,,interval training and finish
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.64,0:04:40.40,Default,,0,0,0,,with a quick run.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.37,0:04:43.02,Default,,0,0,0,,This used to be a multistep
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.02,0:04:44.30,Default,,0,0,0,,process where I would have to
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.30,0:04:45.25,Default,,0,0,0,,finish my workout.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.52,0:04:46.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Then save it.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.64,0:04:47.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Then return to the list of
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.64,0:04:48.26,Default,,0,0,0,,workouts.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.26,0:04:49.79,Default,,0,0,0,,I would find the next one that
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.79,0:04:50.80,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm going to do which is
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.80,0:04:51.91,Default,,0,0,0,,probably not going to be a Quick
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.91,0:04:53.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Start workout at that point.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.28,0:04:54.67,Default,,0,0,0,,So I'm going to have to set a
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.67,0:04:55.78,Default,,0,0,0,,goal and then continue.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.54,0:04:58.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Now it's just a quick tap to add
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.89,0:05:00.58,Default,,0,0,0,,the second workout and another
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.58,0:05:02.19,Default,,0,0,0,,to Quick Start it.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.31,0:05:03.59,Default,,0,0,0,,This is a great example of
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.59,0:05:04.77,Default,,0,0,0,,building a responsive user
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.77,0:05:07.30,Default,,0,0,0,,experience where it's not just
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.30,0:05:08.76,Default,,0,0,0,,about updating the data in your
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.76,0:05:08.96,Default,,0,0,0,,UI.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.53,0:05:10.77,Default,,0,0,0,,It's also about thinking about
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.77,0:05:11.96,Default,,0,0,0,,what the user might want to do
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.96,0:05:13.29,Default,,0,0,0,,next in your app based on what
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.29,0:05:13.98,Default,,0,0,0,,you already know.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.19,0:05:20.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Now the dock is a great place to
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.85,0:05:22.77,Default,,0,0,0,,showcase glanceable information
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.77,0:05:23.71,Default,,0,0,0,,from your app.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.20,0:05:25.45,Default,,0,0,0,,And as you saw in the keynote,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.69,0:05:27.19,Default,,0,0,0,,we've transitioned the dock from
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.19,0:05:29.04,Default,,0,0,0,,being a horizontally scrolled to
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.04,0:05:30.03,Default,,0,0,0,,being vertically scrolled.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.12,0:05:32.34,Default,,0,0,0,,As you'll see in one of the UI
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.34,0:05:33.83,Default,,0,0,0,,updates in WatchKit shortly,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.52,0:05:36.11,Default,,0,0,0,,apps should consider what kind
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.11,0:05:37.93,Default,,0,0,0,,of navigation feels most natural
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.93,0:05:39.49,Default,,0,0,0,,for your app and transition
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.49,0:05:40.00,Default,,0,0,0,,accordingly.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.12,0:05:41.55,Default,,0,0,0,,So that it's really easy to
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.55,0:05:42.93,Default,,0,0,0,,navigate your app either with
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.93,0:05:44.71,Default,,0,0,0,,swipes or by scrolling through
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.71,0:05:44.98,Default,,0,0,0,,information.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.60,0:05:52.47,Default,,0,0,0,,In addition to transitioning to
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.47,0:05:54.87,Default,,0,0,0,,a vertical orientation, the dock
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.87,0:05:56.26,Default,,0,0,0,,also now has two modes of
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.26,0:05:56.78,Default,,0,0,0,,operation.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.26,0:05:58.66,Default,,0,0,0,,There's favorites mode and
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.66,0:05:59.42,Default,,0,0,0,,recents mode.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.29,0:06:01.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Favorites mode will be familiar.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.89,0:06:03.29,Default,,0,0,0,,It operates just like the dock
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.35,0:06:05.71,Default,,0,0,0,,does in watchOS 3 where a user
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.71,0:06:07.60,Default,,0,0,0,,can pick specific apps and the
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.60,0:06:08.84,Default,,0,0,0,,order in which they'd like them
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.84,0:06:10.67,Default,,0,0,0,,to appear in the dock as well as
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.67,0:06:12.26,Default,,0,0,0,,one most recently used slot for
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.50,0:06:13.83,Default,,0,0,0,,the last app that they've used.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.69,0:06:16.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Recents mode will look just like
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.74,0:06:18.15,Default,,0,0,0,,the app switcher on iOS.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.15,0:06:20.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Apps will transition in and out
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.22,0:06:21.48,Default,,0,0,0,,of the dock as you use them
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.48,0:06:22.08,Default,,0,0,0,,throughout the day.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.14,0:06:23.99,Default,,0,0,0,,And that means that you're more
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.99,0:06:25.77,Default,,0,0,0,,likely to see your app show up
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.77,0:06:27.46,Default,,0,0,0,,at some point during the day in
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.46,0:06:28.18,Default,,0,0,0,,the user's dock.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.70,0:06:31.27,Default,,0,0,0,,And that means that it's even
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.27,0:06:32.62,Default,,0,0,0,,more important to make sure that
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.62,0:06:34.30,Default,,0,0,0,,you're updating snapshots using
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.30,0:06:35.84,Default,,0,0,0,,the background snapshot API we
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.84,0:06:37.45,Default,,0,0,0,,introduced last year in watchOS
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.49,0:06:37.73,Default,,0,0,0,,3.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.55,0:06:39.88,Default,,0,0,0,,We're also making enhancements
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.88,0:06:40.39,Default,,0,0,0,,to this API.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.00,0:06:42.45,Default,,0,0,0,,For example, you can now get a
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.45,0:06:45.61,Default,,0,0,0,,callback for when you get a
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.61,0:06:47.30,Default,,0,0,0,,snapshot test to tell whether or
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.30,0:06:48.89,Default,,0,0,0,,not it's a snapshot that you
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.89,0:06:50.60,Default,,0,0,0,,have scheduled or one that's
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.60,0:06:52.21,Default,,0,0,0,,being automatically provided to
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.21,0:06:53.76,Default,,0,0,0,,you but that's triggered by the
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.76,0:06:54.16,Default,,0,0,0,,system.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.29,0:06:57.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Also remember that apps that
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.29,0:06:59.05,Default,,0,0,0,,either in complications or in
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.05,0:07:00.52,Default,,0,0,0,,the dock are launched in the
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.52,0:07:02.32,Default,,0,0,0,,background and suspended but
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.32,0:07:03.03,Default,,0,0,0,,kept in memory.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.47,0:07:05.50,Default,,0,0,0,,So opening them is really fast.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.62,0:07:08.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Now for the rest of our time
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.26,0:07:09.66,Default,,0,0,0,,here today, we're going to talk
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.66,0:07:11.12,Default,,0,0,0,,about three topics that we
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.12,0:07:12.68,Default,,0,0,0,,focused on this year in the
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.68,0:07:13.29,Default,,0,0,0,,WatchSTK.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.45,0:07:16.66,Default,,0,0,0,,The first of them is UI
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.82,0:07:17.51,Default,,0,0,0,,flexibility.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.84,0:07:20.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Giving you more options to
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.51,0:07:22.17,Default,,0,0,0,,present information and actions
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.17,0:07:22.81,Default,,0,0,0,,to users.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.07,0:07:25.84,Default,,0,0,0,,The second is performance.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.47,0:07:27.77,Default,,0,0,0,,So apps always feel as
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.77,0:07:28.98,Default,,0,0,0,,responsive as possible.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.14,0:07:35.20,Default,,0,0,0,,And finally background
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.20,0:07:37.19,Default,,0,0,0,,processing so the users can
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.19,0:07:39.41,Default,,0,0,0,,engage in activities beyond the
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.41,0:07:40.90,Default,,0,0,0,,foreground app experience
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.60,0:07:43.94,Default,,0,0,0,,whether it's in the dock in a
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.94,0:07:46.14,Default,,0,0,0,,complication or in an ongoing
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.14,0:07:46.98,Default,,0,0,0,,task like a workout.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.43,0:07:52.51,Default,,0,0,0,,First let's take a look at UI
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.51,0:07:53.12,Default,,0,0,0,,flexibility.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.94,0:07:55.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Now WatchKit provides a focused
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.63,0:07:57.37,Default,,0,0,0,,set of UI components that have
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.37,0:07:58.58,Default,,0,0,0,,been optimized for the Watch
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.58,0:07:58.94,Default,,0,0,0,,screen.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.42,0:08:00.51,Default,,0,0,0,,But we want to make sure that
Dialogue: 0,0:08:00.51,0:08:01.84,Default,,0,0,0,,those are flexible enough for
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.84,0:08:03.15,Default,,0,0,0,,you to create custom user
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.15,0:08:04.61,Default,,0,0,0,,interfaces that meet the
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.61,0:08:06.59,Default,,0,0,0,,personality of your app.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.71,0:08:09.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Now if you've already created a
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.22,0:08:10.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Watch app or you're new to
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.82,0:08:12.00,Default,,0,0,0,,developing on the platform,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.19,0:08:13.76,Default,,0,0,0,,you're going to love how easy it
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.81,0:08:15.03,Default,,0,0,0,,is to take advantage of the new
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.03,0:08:16.98,Default,,0,0,0,,UI capabilities in watchOS 4.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.98,0:08:18.63,Default,,0,0,0,,And if you're a parent, I'm
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.63,0:08:19.82,Default,,0,0,0,,going to show you how to get
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.82,0:08:21.32,Default,,0,0,0,,workout credit for the things
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.32,0:08:22.45,Default,,0,0,0,,you're probably already doing
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.45,0:08:23.25,Default,,0,0,0,,around the house.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.54,0:08:26.62,Default,,0,0,0,,More on that in just a second.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.67,0:08:27.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Now I have a 4-year-old and
Dialogue: 0,0:08:27.74,0:08:28.65,Default,,0,0,0,,1-year-old at home.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.99,0:08:31.39,Default,,0,0,0,,And often times between work and
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.39,0:08:33.03,Default,,0,0,0,,wrangling the kids, I don't find
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.09,0:08:34.53,Default,,0,0,0,,time during the day to do a
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.53,0:08:36.96,Default,,0,0,0,,formal workout but honestly, a
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.96,0:08:38.48,Default,,0,0,0,,lot of what I find myself doing
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.48,0:08:39.68,Default,,0,0,0,,feels an awful lot like a
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.68,0:08:41.54,Default,,0,0,0,,workout whether it's piggyback
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.54,0:08:42.81,Default,,0,0,0,,rides or cleaning up toys.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.29,0:08:45.30,Default,,0,0,0,,So I created a new app that lets
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.30,0:08:46.22,Default,,0,0,0,,me track these more
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.22,0:08:47.55,Default,,0,0,0,,non-traditional workouts.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.95,0:08:49.24,Default,,0,0,0,,And we're going to use this as
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.24,0:08:50.63,Default,,0,0,0,,an example to see some of the
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.63,0:08:52.66,Default,,0,0,0,,new UI capabilities in watchOS
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.66,0:08:52.91,Default,,0,0,0,,4.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.91,0:08:56.50,Default,,0,0,0,,So here we have a simple
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.50,0:08:57.79,Default,,0,0,0,,in-workout interface.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.23,0:08:59.53,Default,,0,0,0,,It's showing me the calorie
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.53,0:09:00.90,Default,,0,0,0,,counter in the middle as well as
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.90,0:09:03.11,Default,,0,0,0,,a time label and a SpriteKit
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.11,0:09:04.76,Default,,0,0,0,,scene of a child being chased by
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.76,0:09:05.95,Default,,0,0,0,,their parents around the screen.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.00,0:09:08.19,Default,,0,0,0,,This is the kind of interface
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.19,0:09:09.31,Default,,0,0,0,,that's really hard to do in
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.31,0:09:10.91,Default,,0,0,0,,watchOS because you can't
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.91,0:09:12.36,Default,,0,0,0,,overlap interface elements.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.73,0:09:13.83,Default,,0,0,0,,So let's take a look at what's
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.86,0:09:14.54,Default,,0,0,0,,going on here.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.10,0:09:22.91,Default,,0,0,0,,So here we have a group in front
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.96,0:09:24.15,Default,,0,0,0,,containing the labels that I
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.15,0:09:24.60,Default,,0,0,0,,mentioned.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.97,0:09:26.51,Default,,0,0,0,,And that's on top of a SpriteKit
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.51,0:09:26.77,Default,,0,0,0,,scene.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.46,0:09:28.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Now I know you're thinking I
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.39,0:09:29.68,Default,,0,0,0,,just said you can't overlap
Dialogue: 0,0:09:29.68,0:09:30.60,Default,,0,0,0,,interface elements.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.29,0:09:32.95,Default,,0,0,0,,In watchOS 4, we've created a
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.95,0:09:34.87,Default,,0,0,0,,new group layout that allows you
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.87,0:09:36.62,Default,,0,0,0,,to do things like this.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.77,0:09:37.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's take a look at interface
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.95,0:09:39.28,Default,,0,0,0,,builder to see how you can use
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.28,0:09:40.15,Default,,0,0,0,,that.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.16,0:09:43.89,Default,,0,0,0,,So a new option has been added
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.89,0:09:44.41,Default,,0,0,0,,to groups.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.56,0:09:46.32,Default,,0,0,0,,So in addition to vertical and
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.32,0:09:48.00,Default,,0,0,0,,horizontal layouts, you can now
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.00,0:09:48.99,Default,,0,0,0,,select overlap.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.12,0:09:51.12,Default,,0,0,0,,And when selected, overlap
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.12,0:09:52.77,Default,,0,0,0,,groups do not compute offsets
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.77,0:09:54.15,Default,,0,0,0,,for each individual element.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.72,0:09:57.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Instead, you can select their
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.01,0:09:58.46,Default,,0,0,0,,individual alignments like top,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.46,0:09:59.80,Default,,0,0,0,,center, and bottom or left,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.80,0:10:01.46,Default,,0,0,0,,center, and right, and the
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.46,0:10:02.94,Default,,0,0,0,,elements are laid out according
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.94,0:10:04.48,Default,,0,0,0,,to those in a more absolute
Dialogue: 0,0:10:04.48,0:10:05.54,Default,,0,0,0,,fashion within the group.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.93,0:10:09.21,Default,,0,0,0,,And you can also nest groups
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.21,0:10:11.03,Default,,0,0,0,,within each other like I've done
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.03,0:10:12.54,Default,,0,0,0,,here with the metrics group,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.54,0:10:14.16,Default,,0,0,0,,which contains my labels inside
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.16,0:10:14.92,Default,,0,0,0,,of a vertical group.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.09,0:10:16.84,Default,,0,0,0,,And you can also use [inaudible]
Dialogue: 0,0:10:17.30,0:10:20.57,Default,,0,0,0,,and spacing in order to fine
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.57,0:10:21.64,Default,,0,0,0,,tune placement within the
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.64,0:10:22.04,Default,,0,0,0,,groups.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.28,0:10:25.65,Default,,0,0,0,,You can also specify z order by
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.65,0:10:26.83,Default,,0,0,0,,the order in which the elements
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.83,0:10:28.75,Default,,0,0,0,,appear in the outline view as
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.75,0:10:29.17,Default,,0,0,0,,seen here.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.24,0:10:31.56,Default,,0,0,0,,This is going to make a huge
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.56,0:10:32.93,Default,,0,0,0,,difference in making it easier
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.93,0:10:33.93,Default,,0,0,0,,to create custom user
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.93,0:10:34.62,Default,,0,0,0,,interfaces.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.29,0:10:41.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Now in my workout control screen
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.14,0:10:42.24,Default,,0,0,0,,that you'll see here in a
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.75,0:10:44.30,Default,,0,0,0,,second, I've now added a water
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.30,0:10:44.92,Default,,0,0,0,,lock button.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.57,0:10:46.82,Default,,0,0,0,,And water lock can be really
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.82,0:10:48.42,Default,,0,0,0,,helpful for rejecting false
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.42,0:10:50.24,Default,,0,0,0,,touches from water being on the
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.24,0:10:50.62,Default,,0,0,0,,screen.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.26,0:10:52.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Or in my case because my
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.46,0:10:53.61,Default,,0,0,0,,daughter's usually trying to eat
Dialogue: 0,0:10:53.61,0:10:55.96,Default,,0,0,0,,my watch [laughter] but
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.04,0:10:58.77,Default,,0,0,0,,previously in workout apps for
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.77,0:11:00.49,Default,,0,0,0,,third parties, for a user to
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.49,0:11:02.23,Default,,0,0,0,,engage water lock you'd have to
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.35,0:11:04.01,Default,,0,0,0,,start the workout, go back out
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.01,0:11:05.81,Default,,0,0,0,,to the Watch face, swipe up to
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.81,0:11:07.27,Default,,0,0,0,,reveal control center, and then
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.27,0:11:08.23,Default,,0,0,0,,enable water lock.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.85,0:11:10.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Then the next time that you
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.12,0:11:11.41,Default,,0,0,0,,raised your wrist, the workout
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.41,0:11:12.36,Default,,0,0,0,,app would be on the screen.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.90,0:11:13.79,Default,,0,0,0,,We're going to make that a lot
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.79,0:11:15.67,Default,,0,0,0,,easier in watchOS 4 and now you
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.67,0:11:17.53,Default,,0,0,0,,can include a button within your
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.53,0:11:19.34,Default,,0,0,0,,own user interface so that it
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.34,0:11:20.50,Default,,0,0,0,,fits the personality of your
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.30,0:11:21.37,Default,,0,0,0,,app.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.28,0:11:24.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Now water lock can only be
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.02,0:11:25.83,Default,,0,0,0,,enabled by developers, never
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.83,0:11:26.43,Default,,0,0,0,,disabled.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.82,0:11:28.36,Default,,0,0,0,,The user has to do that
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.36,0:11:29.00,Default,,0,0,0,,themselves.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.41,0:11:32.38,Default,,0,0,0,,When they try to interact with
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.38,0:11:33.56,Default,,0,0,0,,the side button or digital
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.56,0:11:35.60,Default,,0,0,0,,crown, an overlay will appear
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.60,0:11:36.66,Default,,0,0,0,,just like the one seen here.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.98,0:11:38.05,Default,,0,0,0,,It's the same one that's used by
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.05,0:11:39.23,Default,,0,0,0,,the system currently.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.22,0:11:41.70,Default,,0,0,0,,And it tells them how to disable
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.70,0:11:42.26,Default,,0,0,0,,water lock.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.44,0:11:44.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Water lock can be enabled in
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.75,0:11:46.60,Default,,0,0,0,,workout as well as in one other
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.60,0:11:47.91,Default,,0,0,0,,session based activity that
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.91,0:11:49.72,Default,,0,0,0,,we'll get to in a little bit in
Dialogue: 0,0:11:49.72,0:11:50.44,Default,,0,0,0,,the presentation.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.92,0:11:52.76,Default,,0,0,0,,And the reason for this is
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.76,0:11:54.13,Default,,0,0,0,,because apps that are not in a
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.13,0:11:56.21,Default,,0,0,0,,workout session, after a period
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.21,0:11:57.77,Default,,0,0,0,,of time and when the wrist has
Dialogue: 0,0:11:57.77,0:11:59.26,Default,,0,0,0,,been dropped, the app will be
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.26,0:12:00.45,Default,,0,0,0,,suspended in the background.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.91,0:12:02.09,Default,,0,0,0,,So when the user raises their
Dialogue: 0,0:12:02.09,0:12:03.58,Default,,0,0,0,,wrist, they won't see the app
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.58,0:12:05.34,Default,,0,0,0,,anymore and the screen is locked
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.34,0:12:06.67,Default,,0,0,0,,so they can't open it back up
Dialogue: 0,0:12:07.49,0:12:09.67,Default,,0,0,0,,but with a workout app, the app
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.67,0:12:11.47,Default,,0,0,0,,will always appear every time
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.47,0:12:12.80,Default,,0,0,0,,they raise their wrist.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.45,0:12:14.49,Default,,0,0,0,,So I can see up-to-date
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.49,0:12:15.95,Default,,0,0,0,,information in -- from my
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.95,0:12:18.78,Default,,0,0,0,,workout as I'm going through it
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.87,0:12:19.77,Default,,0,0,0,,even though the screen is
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.77,0:12:20.04,Default,,0,0,0,,locked.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.65,0:12:21.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's take a look at how to
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.74,0:12:22.85,Default,,0,0,0,,enable this in code.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.41,0:12:29.74,Default,,0,0,0,,As you can see, it's pretty
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.74,0:12:30.62,Default,,0,0,0,,simple to enable.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.73,0:12:32.21,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a single call on the shared
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.21,0:12:33.00,Default,,0,0,0,,extension object.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.99,0:12:36.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Now one last thing to note is
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.17,0:12:38.29,Default,,0,0,0,,that water lock can only be
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.32,0:12:39.82,Default,,0,0,0,,enabled while the app is in the
Dialogue: 0,0:12:39.82,0:12:40.39,Default,,0,0,0,,foreground.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.39,0:12:42.19,Default,,0,0,0,,So the user is always aware of
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.19,0:12:42.96,Default,,0,0,0,,what's going on.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:43.86,0:12:46.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Now here you can see my app is
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.92,0:12:48.41,Default,,0,0,0,,giving me a congratulatory fist
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.41,0:12:50.20,Default,,0,0,0,,bump for figuring out a way to
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.20,0:12:51.53,Default,,0,0,0,,fit in a workout into my
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.53,0:12:52.81,Default,,0,0,0,,parenting responsibilities.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.66,0:12:55.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Now this might be something that
Dialogue: 0,0:12:55.03,0:12:56.44,Default,,0,0,0,,I'd like to show someone else
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.03,0:12:58.09,Default,,0,0,0,,but my options are kind of
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.09,0:12:59.28,Default,,0,0,0,,limited on watchOS.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.28,0:13:00.65,Default,,0,0,0,,I can either do this awkward
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.65,0:13:01.73,Default,,0,0,0,,gesture where I try and keep the
Dialogue: 0,0:13:01.73,0:13:02.97,Default,,0,0,0,,screen on while I turn it away
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.97,0:13:05.01,Default,,0,0,0,,from myself or I can turn it
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.01,0:13:06.94,Default,,0,0,0,,over and tap on the screen but
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.94,0:13:08.35,Default,,0,0,0,,the content is upside down.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.41,0:13:11.62,Default,,0,0,0,,In watchOS 4, we're giving you
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.62,0:13:13.12,Default,,0,0,0,,the ability to turn on auto
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.12,0:13:13.57,Default,,0,0,0,,rotate.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.32,0:13:16.54,Default,,0,0,0,,When enabled, wrist movement
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.54,0:13:18.17,Default,,0,0,0,,will not turn off the screen.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.17,0:13:19.46,Default,,0,0,0,,And we automatically rotate the
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.46,0:13:20.62,Default,,0,0,0,,content when your wrist is
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.62,0:13:21.53,Default,,0,0,0,,turned away from you.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.08,0:13:24.41,Default,,0,0,0,,This will not keep the screen on
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.41,0:13:25.17,Default,,0,0,0,,indefinitely.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.86,0:13:27.38,Default,,0,0,0,,The idle timer will still sleep
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.38,0:13:28.95,Default,,0,0,0,,the display after a period of
Dialogue: 0,0:13:28.95,0:13:30.38,Default,,0,0,0,,inactivity but you should have
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.44,0:13:31.62,Default,,0,0,0,,plenty of time to show the
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.62,0:13:32.97,Default,,0,0,0,,content on your watch to someone
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.97,0:13:33.27,Default,,0,0,0,,else.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.39,0:13:35.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's take a look at the
Dialogue: 0,0:13:35.37,0:13:35.84,Default,,0,0,0,,property.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.46,0:13:38.49,Default,,0,0,0,,You're going to start to see a
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.49,0:13:39.32,Default,,0,0,0,,bit of a theme here.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.60,0:13:40.61,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't have to do a lot of
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.61,0:13:41.93,Default,,0,0,0,,work to take advantage of a lot
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.93,0:13:42.91,Default,,0,0,0,,of the UI capabilities that
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.91,0:13:44.48,Default,,0,0,0,,we're adding in watchOS 4.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:45.30,0:13:47.24,Default,,0,0,0,,There's a lot of applications of
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.24,0:13:47.57,Default,,0,0,0,,this.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.62,0:13:48.58,Default,,0,0,0,,So let's take a look at a few
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.58,0:13:49.14,Default,,0,0,0,,examples.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.08,0:13:52.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Proloquo4Text is a text based
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.51,0:13:54.51,Default,,0,0,0,,communication app that gives
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.51,0:13:56.18,Default,,0,0,0,,literate children, teens, and
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.18,0:13:58.21,Default,,0,0,0,,adults the ability to speak
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.21,0:13:59.39,Default,,0,0,0,,without voice.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.83,0:14:01.73,Default,,0,0,0,,The app allows them to tap on
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.73,0:14:03.60,Default,,0,0,0,,preprogrammed personal phrases
Dialogue: 0,0:14:03.93,0:14:05.03,Default,,0,0,0,,and turn their wrist towards
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.03,0:14:06.64,Default,,0,0,0,,another person to communicate
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.78,0:14:07.92,Default,,0,0,0,,with a text on their wrist.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:08.67,0:14:10.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Here I can place my coffee order
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.41,0:14:12.56,Default,,0,0,0,,by showing my wrist to the
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.56,0:14:14.15,Default,,0,0,0,,cashier and having the text
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.15,0:14:15.90,Default,,0,0,0,,remain on screen and upright
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.90,0:14:17.26,Default,,0,0,0,,when I turn it away from myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.81,0:14:20.41,Default,,0,0,0,,I can even pay for my order
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.41,0:14:22.21,Default,,0,0,0,,using the Starbucks app.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.03,0:14:24.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Starbucks lets me open my
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.59,0:14:26.44,Default,,0,0,0,,barcode from my personal card
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.53,0:14:28.24,Default,,0,0,0,,and have that shown on screen.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.32,0:14:30.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Then I can show that to the
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.44,0:14:32.70,Default,,0,0,0,,scanner at the cashier and have
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.70,0:14:34.34,Default,,0,0,0,,it remain on screen so that it
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.34,0:14:35.49,Default,,0,0,0,,can read it.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:35.82,0:14:36.76,Default,,0,0,0,,There's a ton of different
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.76,0:14:37.72,Default,,0,0,0,,applications of this.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.72,0:14:39.15,Default,,0,0,0,,So you should consider what
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.15,0:14:40.60,Default,,0,0,0,,content in your application
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.60,0:14:41.44,Default,,0,0,0,,might be applicable.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.04,0:14:44.92,Default,,0,0,0,,In our next step, we have a new
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.92,0:14:46.85,Default,,0,0,0,,style for paging views, a
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.85,0:14:47.71,Default,,0,0,0,,vertical paging view.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.71,0:14:51.12,Default,,0,0,0,,I could have implemented this as
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.12,0:14:52.74,Default,,0,0,0,,a scroll view but really these
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.74,0:14:54.13,Default,,0,0,0,,are two distinct pages.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.26,0:14:55.45,Default,,0,0,0,,And it's great how they just
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.45,0:14:56.42,Default,,0,0,0,,snap into place.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.95,0:14:58.73,Default,,0,0,0,,It's also really natural to use
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.73,0:14:59.60,Default,,0,0,0,,with the digital crown.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.54,0:15:01.81,Default,,0,0,0,,And the animation between the
Dialogue: 0,0:15:01.81,0:15:03.88,Default,,0,0,0,,pages is very similar to the one
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.88,0:15:05.46,Default,,0,0,0,,we introduced last year for
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.46,0:15:07.19,Default,,0,0,0,,performing segues between table
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.19,0:15:08.92,Default,,0,0,0,,rows in a master detail
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.92,0:15:10.99,Default,,0,0,0,,application but now you can do
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.99,0:15:12.55,Default,,0,0,0,,so without using a navigation
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.55,0:15:12.98,Default,,0,0,0,,controller.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:15.22,0:15:17.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's take a look at how you
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.20,0:15:18.40,Default,,0,0,0,,implement this interface.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.98,0:15:21.64,Default,,0,0,0,,So we replaced the reload root
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.64,0:15:22.89,Default,,0,0,0,,controller's method with a new
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.89,0:15:24.89,Default,,0,0,0,,one that takes in two key pieces
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.89,0:15:25.85,Default,,0,0,0,,of new information.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.51,0:15:28.16,Default,,0,0,0,,The first is the ability to set
Dialogue: 0,0:15:28.16,0:15:28.99,Default,,0,0,0,,the orientation.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.22,0:15:30.68,Default,,0,0,0,,So you use the same method
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.68,0:15:31.82,Default,,0,0,0,,whether you're doing it in a
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.82,0:15:33.53,Default,,0,0,0,,horizontal paging view or a
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.53,0:15:34.42,Default,,0,0,0,,vertical paging view.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:35.52,0:15:36.92,Default,,0,0,0,,And the second one is something
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.92,0:15:37.95,Default,,0,0,0,,that we've heard a lot of
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.95,0:15:39.68,Default,,0,0,0,,feedback about and we're excited
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.68,0:15:40.97,Default,,0,0,0,,to be able to offer in watchOS
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.97,0:15:41.25,Default,,0,0,0,,4.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:41.35,0:15:42.71,Default,,0,0,0,,And that's the ability to set
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.71,0:15:44.15,Default,,0,0,0,,the initial page index.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.74,0:15:46.26,Default,,0,0,0,,So this is great for things like
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.26,0:15:47.64,Default,,0,0,0,,workout apps where you want a
Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.64,0:15:48.57,Default,,0,0,0,,main workout UI.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.57,0:15:52.73,Default,,0,0,0,,[Applause] I know we've seen
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.80,0:15:53.69,Default,,0,0,0,,lots of radars.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:54.92,0:15:56.17,Default,,0,0,0,,And you want the control screen
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.17,0:15:57.48,Default,,0,0,0,,left to center but you want to
Dialogue: 0,0:15:57.48,0:15:58.76,Default,,0,0,0,,load directly into the main
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.76,0:15:59.33,Default,,0,0,0,,workout UI.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:00.11,0:16:01.19,Default,,0,0,0,,So this allows you to set the
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.19,0:16:02.68,Default,,0,0,0,,index to wherever you want and
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.68,0:16:03.83,Default,,0,0,0,,have it load directly there.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.05,0:16:09.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Now here we have a history view.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.14,0:16:11.54,Default,,0,0,0,,And when doing an interface like
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.54,0:16:12.96,Default,,0,0,0,,this where we may have hundreds
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.96,0:16:14.39,Default,,0,0,0,,of records, there's a couple of
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.39,0:16:15.64,Default,,0,0,0,,things to keep in mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.17,0:16:17.74,Default,,0,0,0,,The first is storage.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.89,0:16:19.14,Default,,0,0,0,,I probably don't want to store
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.14,0:16:20.49,Default,,0,0,0,,all of my workouts that I've
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.49,0:16:22.44,Default,,0,0,0,,ever completed on the watch when
Dialogue: 0,0:16:22.44,0:16:24.09,Default,,0,0,0,,I can easily load them using
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.09,0:16:25.04,Default,,0,0,0,,watch connectivity from the
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.04,0:16:26.58,Default,,0,0,0,,phone or from a server.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.92,0:16:29.53,Default,,0,0,0,,The second is performance.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:30.08,0:16:31.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Loading too many table rows at
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.50,0:16:34.16,Default,,0,0,0,,once can lead -- load -- lead to
Dialogue: 0,0:16:34.16,0:16:35.48,Default,,0,0,0,,a decrease in performance and
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.48,0:16:36.48,Default,,0,0,0,,load time for the table.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.10,0:16:44.06,Default,,0,0,0,,So here we're now allowing you
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.19,0:16:45.72,Default,,0,0,0,,to get callbacks for when the
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.72,0:16:47.36,Default,,0,0,0,,user scrolls to the bottom of
Dialogue: 0,0:16:47.36,0:16:48.47,Default,,0,0,0,,the screen or the top of the
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.47,0:16:48.90,Default,,0,0,0,,screen.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.90,0:16:50.25,Default,,0,0,0,,So you can do things like I have
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.25,0:16:51.71,Default,,0,0,0,,here where I'm getting the
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.71,0:16:52.29,Default,,0,0,0,,callback.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.69,0:16:54.11,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm loading -- putting on a
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.11,0:16:55.40,Default,,0,0,0,,loading indicator and then I'm
Dialogue: 0,0:16:55.40,0:16:56.89,Default,,0,0,0,,loading data from the phone.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.43,0:17:00.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's take a look at how you can
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.46,0:17:01.68,Default,,0,0,0,,implement these callbacks.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:06.44,0:17:07.74,Default,,0,0,0,,So the first one is the one I
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.74,0:17:09.02,Default,,0,0,0,,was just using in the last user
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.02,0:17:09.53,Default,,0,0,0,,interface.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:10.06,0:17:11.81,Default,,0,0,0,,InterfaceOffsetDidScrollToTop.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.37,0:17:13.26,Default,,0,0,0,,This gets called when the
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.26,0:17:14.72,Default,,0,0,0,,animation completes, when the
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.72,0:17:16.49,Default,,0,0,0,,user scrolls all the way to the
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.49,0:17:17.25,Default,,0,0,0,,bottom of the screen.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.18,0:17:19.31,Default,,0,0,0,,The second is the exact
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.31,0:17:19.82,Default,,0,0,0,,opposite,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.92,0:17:21.77,Default,,0,0,0,,interfaceOffsetDidScrollToTop
Dialogue: 0,0:17:22.05,0:17:22.93,Default,,0,0,0,,which gets called when you
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.19,0:17:24.20,Default,,0,0,0,,scroll to the top of the screen.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.35,0:17:25.67,Default,,0,0,0,,And the last one,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.67,0:17:27.29,Default,,0,0,0,,interfaceDidScrollToTop gets
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.29,0:17:28.93,Default,,0,0,0,,called when the user taps on the
Dialogue: 0,0:17:28.93,0:17:30.51,Default,,0,0,0,,status bar, which scrolls the
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.51,0:17:31.44,Default,,0,0,0,,interface all the way to the
Dialogue: 0,0:17:31.44,0:17:31.71,Default,,0,0,0,,top.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:32.34,0:17:33.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Now we've also included in a
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.83,0:17:35.43,Default,,0,0,0,,scroll function, which lets you
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.43,0:17:38.33,Default,,0,0,0,,pass in an interface element and
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.39,0:17:40.04,Default,,0,0,0,,have it scrolls to appear at
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.04,0:17:41.26,Default,,0,0,0,,either the top, center, or
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.26,0:17:42.07,Default,,0,0,0,,bottom of the screen.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.84,0:17:44.61,Default,,0,0,0,,I use that in my history view to
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.61,0:17:45.74,Default,,0,0,0,,show loading indicator.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.51,0:17:47.45,Default,,0,0,0,,When I loaded the group that
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.45,0:17:49.13,Default,,0,0,0,,contained my animation, it
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.13,0:17:50.04,Default,,0,0,0,,loaded off screen.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.23,0:17:51.84,Default,,0,0,0,,So I passed it into the scroll
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.84,0:17:54.03,Default,,0,0,0,,method and set it to show at the
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.03,0:17:54.83,Default,,0,0,0,,bottom of the screen.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.00,0:17:58.71,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.21,0:18:01.08,Default,,0,0,0,,And here we have a reimagined
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.86,0:18:03.39,Default,,0,0,0,,post workout screen that's been
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.39,0:18:04.97,Default,,0,0,0,,redesigned as a full screen
Dialogue: 0,0:18:04.97,0:18:05.52,Default,,0,0,0,,animation.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:06.53,0:18:08.73,Default,,0,0,0,,In watchOS 4 for SpriteKit and
Dialogue: 0,0:18:08.73,0:18:10.27,Default,,0,0,0,,SyncIt [phonetic] apps, you can
Dialogue: 0,0:18:10.27,0:18:11.82,Default,,0,0,0,,now make use of the entire
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.82,0:18:12.28,Default,,0,0,0,,display.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.66,0:18:15.52,Default,,0,0,0,,It is still a watch though, so
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.52,0:18:16.78,Default,,0,0,0,,we are always going to display
Dialogue: 0,0:18:16.78,0:18:18.98,Default,,0,0,0,,the time in the top corner with
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.98,0:18:20.53,Default,,0,0,0,,a gradient behind it so the user
Dialogue: 0,0:18:20.53,0:18:22.12,Default,,0,0,0,,can always read the display
Dialogue: 0,0:18:22.49,0:18:23.49,Default,,0,0,0,,regardless of the color of
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.49,0:18:25.05,Default,,0,0,0,,content behind it.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.45,0:18:28.03,Default,,0,0,0,,As you can see, there's a lot of
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.03,0:18:29.86,Default,,0,0,0,,new changes in creating your
Dialogue: 0,0:18:29.86,0:18:31.65,Default,,0,0,0,,user interfaces in watchOS 4.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.81,0:18:33.39,Default,,0,0,0,,I encourage you to check out a
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.39,0:18:35.30,Default,,0,0,0,,session later this week on
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.96,0:18:38.38,Default,,0,0,0,,planning a great Watch
Dialogue: 0,0:18:38.38,0:18:40.15,Default,,0,0,0,,experience, which will be going
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.15,0:18:41.73,Default,,0,0,0,,through planning both the
Dialogue: 0,0:18:41.73,0:18:43.01,Default,,0,0,0,,interactions that you should do
Dialogue: 0,0:18:43.01,0:18:44.73,Default,,0,0,0,,on a Watch as well as the design
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.73,0:18:45.49,Default,,0,0,0,,of the application.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.26,0:18:48.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Next, let's take a look at
Dialogue: 0,0:18:48.24,0:18:48.85,Default,,0,0,0,,performance.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.58,0:18:51.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Now interactions on watches
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.19,0:18:52.34,Default,,0,0,0,,we've talked about previously,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:52.48,0:18:54.02,Default,,0,0,0,,are short but numerous.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.50,0:18:55.70,Default,,0,0,0,,So we always want to make sure
Dialogue: 0,0:18:55.70,0:18:57.01,Default,,0,0,0,,that we're both preparing ahead
Dialogue: 0,0:18:57.48,0:18:58.75,Default,,0,0,0,,but we're also as responsive as
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.75,0:18:59.25,Default,,0,0,0,,possible.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.79,0:19:02.83,Default,,0,0,0,,And to that end, in watchOS 2,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.29,0:19:04.61,Default,,0,0,0,,we moved the extension from
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.61,0:19:06.15,Default,,0,0,0,,running on the phone to running
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.15,0:19:06.79,Default,,0,0,0,,on the Watch.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:07.25,0:19:08.61,Default,,0,0,0,,And that did a couple of things.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.99,0:19:10.39,Default,,0,0,0,,It meant that you could run the
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.39,0:19:11.90,Default,,0,0,0,,app when the phone was no longer
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.90,0:19:13.99,Default,,0,0,0,,present but it also meant lower
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.99,0:19:15.31,Default,,0,0,0,,latency and communication.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.37,0:19:19.15,Default,,0,0,0,,The behind the scenes, the app
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.41,0:19:21.19,Default,,0,0,0,,and extension are still running
Dialogue: 0,0:19:21.19,0:19:22.86,Default,,0,0,0,,in separate processes where your
Dialogue: 0,0:19:22.86,0:19:24.49,Default,,0,0,0,,code is trying to make updates
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.62,0:19:25.86,Default,,0,0,0,,and you're responding to events.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.86,0:19:27.21,Default,,0,0,0,,So there's latency in the
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.21,0:19:28.51,Default,,0,0,0,,communication for the inner
Dialogue: 0,0:19:28.51,0:19:29.54,Default,,0,0,0,,process communication between
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.54,0:19:29.76,Default,,0,0,0,,the two.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.76,0:19:32.28,Default,,0,0,0,,With a little bit of magic in
Dialogue: 0,0:19:32.28,0:19:34.92,Default,,0,0,0,,watchOS 4, at run time, we're
Dialogue: 0,0:19:34.92,0:19:36.55,Default,,0,0,0,,loading both the extension and
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.55,0:19:38.18,Default,,0,0,0,,the app into the same process.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.63,0:19:40.25,Default,,0,0,0,,This is going to make a huge
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.25,0:19:41.35,Default,,0,0,0,,difference in performance of
Dialogue: 0,0:19:41.35,0:19:41.92,Default,,0,0,0,,your apps.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.36,0:19:43.74,Default,,0,0,0,,You should see things like lower
Dialogue: 0,0:19:43.74,0:19:45.74,Default,,0,0,0,,touch latency, faster loading of
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.74,0:19:47.75,Default,,0,0,0,,views as well as higher frame
Dialogue: 0,0:19:47.75,0:19:48.72,Default,,0,0,0,,rates while you're interacting
Dialogue: 0,0:19:48.72,0:19:49.36,Default,,0,0,0,,with the device.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:49.36,0:19:51.75,Default,,0,0,0,,And the best part is you don't
Dialogue: 0,0:19:51.75,0:19:53.06,Default,,0,0,0,,have to do anything for your
Dialogue: 0,0:19:53.06,0:19:54.22,Default,,0,0,0,,users to gain from this.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:54.60,0:19:55.98,Default,,0,0,0,,This is a completely binary
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.98,0:19:58.07,Default,,0,0,0,,compatible change for all apps
Dialogue: 0,0:19:58.07,0:19:59.22,Default,,0,0,0,,watchOS 2 and later.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:59.96,0:20:01.55,Default,,0,0,0,,That means no updates.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.18,0:20:03.17,Default,,0,0,0,,[Applause] No recompiling.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:04.67,0:20:06.45,Default,,0,0,0,,All existing apps either on a
Dialogue: 0,0:20:06.45,0:20:07.97,Default,,0,0,0,,user's device or in the App
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.97,0:20:09.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Store are just going to start
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.14,0:20:10.67,Default,,0,0,0,,benefiting in watchOS 4.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:11.66,0:20:12.86,Default,,0,0,0,,This is going to make a huge
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.86,0:20:13.30,Default,,0,0,0,,difference.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.30,0:20:14.11,Default,,0,0,0,,So we can't wait for you to
Dialogue: 0,0:20:14.11,0:20:15.25,Default,,0,0,0,,check it out.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:16.65,0:20:17.83,Default,,0,0,0,,I moved too far away.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:18.46,0:20:20.42,Default,,0,0,0,,And finally let's take a look at
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.42,0:20:21.34,Default,,0,0,0,,background processing.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.20,0:20:23.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Like I said before, it's really
Dialogue: 0,0:20:23.47,0:20:25.05,Default,,0,0,0,,important to prepare ahead of
Dialogue: 0,0:20:25.05,0:20:27.04,Default,,0,0,0,,time and making sure that the
Dialogue: 0,0:20:27.04,0:20:28.45,Default,,0,0,0,,app is always up-to-date
Dialogue: 0,0:20:28.45,0:20:29.64,Default,,0,0,0,,whenever the user wants to look
Dialogue: 0,0:20:29.64,0:20:30.18,Default,,0,0,0,,at their wrist.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:30.88,0:20:31.88,Default,,0,0,0,,And this can be done with a
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.88,0:20:33.15,Default,,0,0,0,,combination of background
Dialogue: 0,0:20:33.15,0:20:34.68,Default,,0,0,0,,running modes, use of the
Dialogue: 0,0:20:34.68,0:20:36.91,Default,,0,0,0,,complication, and snapshot APIs
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.91,0:20:38.33,Default,,0,0,0,,as well as some changes that
Dialogue: 0,0:20:38.33,0:20:39.76,Default,,0,0,0,,we're making this year for what
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.76,0:20:41.44,Default,,0,0,0,,will be called the Frontmost App
Dialogue: 0,0:20:41.44,0:20:41.79,Default,,0,0,0,,State.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:42.31,0:20:43.47,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll get to that in just a few
Dialogue: 0,0:20:43.47,0:20:43.91,Default,,0,0,0,,minutes.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:44.29,0:20:47.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Now last year we introduced the
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.65,0:20:49.09,Default,,0,0,0,,workout processing background
Dialogue: 0,0:20:49.09,0:20:50.97,Default,,0,0,0,,mode allowing third party apps
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.97,0:20:52.43,Default,,0,0,0,,to run in the background and
Dialogue: 0,0:20:52.43,0:20:54.00,Default,,0,0,0,,making the app available every
Dialogue: 0,0:20:54.00,0:20:55.10,Default,,0,0,0,,time the user raised their
Dialogue: 0,0:20:55.10,0:20:55.43,Default,,0,0,0,,wrist.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:56.30,0:20:58.09,Default,,0,0,0,,We're continuing to make these
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.09,0:20:59.94,Default,,0,0,0,,APIs better this year by adding
Dialogue: 0,0:20:59.94,0:21:01.02,Default,,0,0,0,,a few new additions.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:01.86,0:21:03.66,Default,,0,0,0,,The first is a hardware pause
Dialogue: 0,0:21:03.66,0:21:04.58,Default,,0,0,0,,and resume API.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:05.43,0:21:06.65,Default,,0,0,0,,When a user presses the side
Dialogue: 0,0:21:06.65,0:21:07.90,Default,,0,0,0,,button and digital crown at the
Dialogue: 0,0:21:07.90,0:21:11.05,Default,,0,0,0,,same time, an event is generated
Dialogue: 0,0:21:11.05,0:21:12.43,Default,,0,0,0,,that you can respond to in your
Dialogue: 0,0:21:12.43,0:21:13.02,Default,,0,0,0,,application.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:14.52,0:21:15.60,Default,,0,0,0,,That way you can pause and
Dialogue: 0,0:21:15.60,0:21:17.16,Default,,0,0,0,,resume the workout depending on
Dialogue: 0,0:21:17.16,0:21:19.28,Default,,0,0,0,,which state the session is in.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:21.16,0:21:23.26,Default,,0,0,0,,The second is workout segments.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:23.88,0:21:25.14,Default,,0,0,0,,And this allows you -- it's a
Dialogue: 0,0:21:25.14,0:21:26.16,Default,,0,0,0,,new type on the HK [phonetic]
Dialogue: 0,0:21:26.16,0:21:28.59,Default,,0,0,0,,workout event class and this
Dialogue: 0,0:21:28.59,0:21:30.32,Default,,0,0,0,,allows you to mark important
Dialogue: 0,0:21:30.32,0:21:31.76,Default,,0,0,0,,durations of time within your
Dialogue: 0,0:21:31.76,0:21:32.18,Default,,0,0,0,,workout.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:32.89,0:21:34.06,Default,,0,0,0,,This could be used for things
Dialogue: 0,0:21:34.06,0:21:35.17,Default,,0,0,0,,like marking the different
Dialogue: 0,0:21:35.17,0:21:36.26,Default,,0,0,0,,sections of an interval
Dialogue: 0,0:21:36.26,0:21:37.17,Default,,0,0,0,,training, for example.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:37.81,0:21:40.20,Default,,0,0,0,,And last year we started to
Dialogue: 0,0:21:40.20,0:21:41.59,Default,,0,0,0,,track workout routes for
Dialogue: 0,0:21:41.59,0:21:43.67,Default,,0,0,0,,specific types of workouts using
Dialogue: 0,0:21:43.67,0:21:44.95,Default,,0,0,0,,the Apple Workout app.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:45.52,0:21:46.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Now with a user's permission,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:47.41,0:21:48.97,Default,,0,0,0,,you can both read these workout
Dialogue: 0,0:21:49.02,0:21:50.55,Default,,0,0,0,,routes as well as create your
Dialogue: 0,0:21:50.55,0:21:50.74,Default,,0,0,0,,own.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:51.93,0:21:53.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Now if you already have a
Dialogue: 0,0:21:53.06,0:21:53.88,Default,,0,0,0,,workout app or you're
Dialogue: 0,0:21:53.88,0:21:55.51,Default,,0,0,0,,considering making one, you
Dialogue: 0,0:21:55.51,0:21:56.57,Default,,0,0,0,,should check out the what's new
Dialogue: 0,0:21:56.57,0:21:57.72,Default,,0,0,0,,in health session later this
Dialogue: 0,0:21:57.72,0:21:59.20,Default,,0,0,0,,week which will be going through
Dialogue: 0,0:21:59.20,0:22:01.06,Default,,0,0,0,,how to use these APIs as well as
Dialogue: 0,0:22:01.06,0:22:02.37,Default,,0,0,0,,other changes in HealthKit that
Dialogue: 0,0:22:02.37,0:22:03.97,Default,,0,0,0,,you should take advantage of.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:04.96,0:22:06.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Remember also adding a few new
Dialogue: 0,0:22:06.81,0:22:08.27,Default,,0,0,0,,background modes in WatchKit
Dialogue: 0,0:22:08.27,0:22:08.67,Default,,0,0,0,,this year.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:09.29,0:22:10.65,Default,,0,0,0,,The first of which is a location
Dialogue: 0,0:22:10.65,0:22:11.32,Default,,0,0,0,,background mode.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:11.99,0:22:13.17,Default,,0,0,0,,This is great for things like
Dialogue: 0,0:22:13.17,0:22:15.23,Default,,0,0,0,,location based games as well as
Dialogue: 0,0:22:15.23,0:22:17.78,Default,,0,0,0,,turn-by-turn navigation apps.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:17.99,0:22:19.35,Default,,0,0,0,,And similar to workout apps,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:19.42,0:22:20.94,Default,,0,0,0,,it'll always be available every
Dialogue: 0,0:22:20.94,0:22:22.12,Default,,0,0,0,,time the user raises their
Dialogue: 0,0:22:22.12,0:22:22.44,Default,,0,0,0,,wrist.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:22.44,0:22:24.87,Default,,0,0,0,,And if there's something that
Dialogue: 0,0:22:24.87,0:22:26.15,Default,,0,0,0,,you need to alert the user to
Dialogue: 0,0:22:26.15,0:22:27.16,Default,,0,0,0,,like when I've made a wrong
Dialogue: 0,0:22:27.16,0:22:28.73,Default,,0,0,0,,turn, you can use audio and
Dialogue: 0,0:22:28.73,0:22:30.39,Default,,0,0,0,,haptics from the background in
Dialogue: 0,0:22:30.39,0:22:31.42,Default,,0,0,0,,order to get their attention.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:31.97,0:22:34.79,Default,,0,0,0,,And like I had mentioned before,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:34.79,0:22:35.93,Default,,0,0,0,,there was another session based
Dialogue: 0,0:22:35.93,0:22:38.26,Default,,0,0,0,,activity that you can also water
Dialogue: 0,0:22:38.26,0:22:39.56,Default,,0,0,0,,lock mode with and this is --
Dialogue: 0,0:22:39.56,0:22:40.60,Default,,0,0,0,,that's location mode.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:41.07,0:22:42.39,Default,,0,0,0,,So you can use it in conjunction
Dialogue: 0,0:22:42.39,0:22:43.65,Default,,0,0,0,,with water-based activities.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:44.29,0:22:46.91,Default,,0,0,0,,In order to conserve battery
Dialogue: 0,0:22:46.91,0:22:48.91,Default,,0,0,0,,power, though, CPU in the
Dialogue: 0,0:22:48.91,0:22:50.19,Default,,0,0,0,,background is limited.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:50.36,0:22:51.66,Default,,0,0,0,,So you need to monitor what
Dialogue: 0,0:22:51.66,0:22:52.65,Default,,0,0,0,,things need to be done in the
Dialogue: 0,0:22:52.65,0:22:54.17,Default,,0,0,0,,background and what can be saved
Dialogue: 0,0:22:54.23,0:22:54.70,Default,,0,0,0,,for later.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:55.29,0:22:59.59,Default,,0,0,0,,And lastly, you must start the
Dialogue: 0,0:22:59.59,0:23:01.26,Default,,0,0,0,,location session from the
Dialogue: 0,0:23:01.26,0:23:02.72,Default,,0,0,0,,foreground just like a workout
Dialogue: 0,0:23:03.28,0:23:05.00,Default,,0,0,0,,so that the user's always aware
Dialogue: 0,0:23:05.00,0:23:05.80,Default,,0,0,0,,of what's going on.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:06.32,0:23:07.32,Default,,0,0,0,,And while you're accessing
Dialogue: 0,0:23:07.32,0:23:09.10,Default,,0,0,0,,location, there will be a status
Dialogue: 0,0:23:09.10,0:23:11.10,Default,,0,0,0,,indicator and control center so
Dialogue: 0,0:23:11.10,0:23:12.56,Default,,0,0,0,,that they can always monitor
Dialogue: 0,0:23:12.56,0:23:12.98,Default,,0,0,0,,their privacy.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:16.14,0:23:17.54,Default,,0,0,0,,And we've also added in-line
Dialogue: 0,0:23:17.54,0:23:19.14,Default,,0,0,0,,audio recording as well as a
Dialogue: 0,0:23:19.14,0:23:19.92,Default,,0,0,0,,background mode.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:19.98,0:23:22.70,Default,,0,0,0,,And recording has been available
Dialogue: 0,0:23:22.70,0:23:24.62,Default,,0,0,0,,since watchOS 2 but it was only
Dialogue: 0,0:23:24.62,0:23:26.64,Default,,0,0,0,,offered in a modal form where we
Dialogue: 0,0:23:26.64,0:23:27.96,Default,,0,0,0,,would hand a file back to you
Dialogue: 0,0:23:27.96,0:23:29.18,Default,,0,0,0,,after the user had finished
Dialogue: 0,0:23:29.18,0:23:29.88,Default,,0,0,0,,their recording.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:30.54,0:23:31.59,Default,,0,0,0,,You could also continue
Dialogue: 0,0:23:31.59,0:23:32.68,Default,,0,0,0,,recording when the user had
Dialogue: 0,0:23:32.68,0:23:34.01,Default,,0,0,0,,dropped their wrist but it would
Dialogue: 0,0:23:34.01,0:23:35.03,Default,,0,0,0,,keep the screen on for the
Dialogue: 0,0:23:35.03,0:23:35.82,Default,,0,0,0,,entire time.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:36.62,0:23:38.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Now in watchOS 4, we're offering
Dialogue: 0,0:23:38.73,0:23:40.35,Default,,0,0,0,,in-line audio recording to solve
Dialogue: 0,0:23:40.35,0:23:41.36,Default,,0,0,0,,some of these problems.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:43.10,0:23:45.20,Default,,0,0,0,,First, you no longer are limited
Dialogue: 0,0:23:45.20,0:23:46.59,Default,,0,0,0,,to the modal form so you can
Dialogue: 0,0:23:46.59,0:23:47.69,Default,,0,0,0,,create your own custom U
Dialogue: 0,0:23:47.69,0:23:49.18,Default,,0,0,0,,recording controls that fit the
Dialogue: 0,0:23:49.24,0:23:51.19,Default,,0,0,0,,UI of your app.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:51.48,0:23:52.94,Default,,0,0,0,,You can also do in-line audio
Dialogue: 0,0:23:52.94,0:23:53.52,Default,,0,0,0,,recording.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:53.64,0:23:54.75,Default,,0,0,0,,So if you wanted to look for a
Dialogue: 0,0:23:54.75,0:23:56.33,Default,,0,0,0,,certain signature in the audio
Dialogue: 0,0:23:56.68,0:23:57.89,Default,,0,0,0,,or if you wanted to do things
Dialogue: 0,0:23:57.89,0:23:59.07,Default,,0,0,0,,like real time language
Dialogue: 0,0:23:59.07,0:24:00.14,Default,,0,0,0,,translation on the watch.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:01.45,0:24:02.98,Default,,0,0,0,,And you can continue recording
Dialogue: 0,0:24:02.98,0:24:03.98,Default,,0,0,0,,when the user has dropped their
Dialogue: 0,0:24:03.98,0:24:05.42,Default,,0,0,0,,wrist but now it's a full
Dialogue: 0,0:24:05.42,0:24:06.34,Default,,0,0,0,,background mode.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:06.51,0:24:07.67,Default,,0,0,0,,So you don't need to waste the
Dialogue: 0,0:24:07.67,0:24:09.26,Default,,0,0,0,,additional battery power of
Dialogue: 0,0:24:09.26,0:24:10.14,Default,,0,0,0,,keeping the screen on.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:11.42,0:24:12.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Imagine being able to walk into
Dialogue: 0,0:24:12.75,0:24:14.29,Default,,0,0,0,,classroom and record an entire
Dialogue: 0,0:24:14.29,0:24:15.70,Default,,0,0,0,,lecture right from your wrist.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:16.17,0:24:18.75,Default,,0,0,0,,And similar to other background
Dialogue: 0,0:24:18.75,0:24:21.42,Default,,0,0,0,,modes in watchOS, the app will
Dialogue: 0,0:24:21.42,0:24:22.69,Default,,0,0,0,,always appear every time the
Dialogue: 0,0:24:22.69,0:24:23.86,Default,,0,0,0,,user raises their wrist.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:24.30,0:24:26.39,Default,,0,0,0,,It'll be CPU limited and the app
Dialogue: 0,0:24:26.43,0:24:27.88,Default,,0,0,0,,must be started -- the session
Dialogue: 0,0:24:27.88,0:24:28.69,Default,,0,0,0,,must be started from the
Dialogue: 0,0:24:28.69,0:24:29.19,Default,,0,0,0,,foreground.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:30.01,0:24:31.48,Default,,0,0,0,,And while you're doing a
Dialogue: 0,0:24:31.48,0:24:32.96,Default,,0,0,0,,recording, there will be an
Dialogue: 0,0:24:32.96,0:24:34.64,Default,,0,0,0,,indicator on the watch face that
Dialogue: 0,0:24:34.81,0:24:36.56,Default,,0,0,0,,the user can tap on to return to
Dialogue: 0,0:24:36.56,0:24:38.05,Default,,0,0,0,,the recording app.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:40.28,0:24:41.89,Default,,0,0,0,,These background modes are going
Dialogue: 0,0:24:41.89,0:24:43.15,Default,,0,0,0,,to make a huge difference in
Dialogue: 0,0:24:43.15,0:24:45.23,Default,,0,0,0,,doing ongoing tasks in watchOS
Dialogue: 0,0:24:45.23,0:24:45.47,Default,,0,0,0,,4.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:47.34,0:24:48.42,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:49.81,0:24:51.41,Default,,0,0,0,,We're also supporting core
Dialogue: 0,0:24:51.41,0:24:53.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Bluetooth on Watch -- in watchOS
Dialogue: 0,0:24:53.06,0:24:53.29,Default,,0,0,0,,4.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:53.69,0:24:53.80,Default,,0,0,0,,This --
Dialogue: 0,0:24:54.52,0:24:57.10,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Applause ]
Dialogue: 0,0:24:57.60,0:24:58.47,Default,,0,0,0,,This means you can connect
Dialogue: 0,0:24:58.56,0:25:00.09,Default,,0,0,0,,directly to the Watch from your
Dialogue: 0,0:25:00.09,0:25:00.71,Default,,0,0,0,,devices.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:01.58,0:25:03.72,Default,,0,0,0,,And get updated data with lower
Dialogue: 0,0:25:03.72,0:25:05.83,Default,,0,0,0,,latency as well as continue use
Dialogue: 0,0:25:05.83,0:25:07.62,Default,,0,0,0,,when the phone is no longer
Dialogue: 0,0:25:07.62,0:25:08.02,Default,,0,0,0,,present.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:08.73,0:25:09.92,Default,,0,0,0,,And previously for Bluetooth
Dialogue: 0,0:25:09.92,0:25:11.37,Default,,0,0,0,,devices, you'd have to connect
Dialogue: 0,0:25:11.37,0:25:13.08,Default,,0,0,0,,with the phone and then shuttle
Dialogue: 0,0:25:13.08,0:25:14.13,Default,,0,0,0,,data over using Watch
Dialogue: 0,0:25:14.13,0:25:14.70,Default,,0,0,0,,connectivity.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:15.24,0:25:16.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Now you should get much faster
Dialogue: 0,0:25:16.57,0:25:17.00,Default,,0,0,0,,updates.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:17.30,0:25:18.69,Default,,0,0,0,,And with core Bluetooth on the
Dialogue: 0,0:25:18.69,0:25:20.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Watch, you can connect up to two
Dialogue: 0,0:25:20.37,0:25:21.08,Default,,0,0,0,,peripherals.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:21.93,0:25:23.12,Default,,0,0,0,,And we're only supporting
Dialogue: 0,0:25:23.12,0:25:24.36,Default,,0,0,0,,central mode which means that
Dialogue: 0,0:25:24.36,0:25:26.13,Default,,0,0,0,,you need to -- you can connect
Dialogue: 0,0:25:26.13,0:25:27.74,Default,,0,0,0,,to other devices but the Watch
Dialogue: 0,0:25:27.74,0:25:29.37,Default,,0,0,0,,cannot be used as a peripheral
Dialogue: 0,0:25:29.37,0:25:29.94,Default,,0,0,0,,itself.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:30.46,0:25:32.21,Default,,0,0,0,,And while you're in the
Dialogue: 0,0:25:32.21,0:25:33.77,Default,,0,0,0,,foreground, there's a minimum
Dialogue: 0,0:25:33.77,0:25:35.54,Default,,0,0,0,,time between samples of 30
Dialogue: 0,0:25:35.54,0:25:37.52,Default,,0,0,0,,milliseconds and when used in
Dialogue: 0,0:25:37.52,0:25:38.82,Default,,0,0,0,,conjunction with the background
Dialogue: 0,0:25:38.82,0:25:41.63,Default,,0,0,0,,mode, that time is limited to
Dialogue: 0,0:25:41.63,0:25:43.11,Default,,0,0,0,,120 milliseconds.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:43.82,0:25:46.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Now when used in conjunction
Dialogue: 0,0:25:46.34,0:25:47.35,Default,,0,0,0,,with a background mode,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:47.98,0:25:49.35,Default,,0,0,0,,background running apps can only
Dialogue: 0,0:25:49.35,0:25:50.66,Default,,0,0,0,,connect not scan.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:50.66,0:25:51.97,Default,,0,0,0,,So you need to do your pairing
Dialogue: 0,0:25:51.97,0:25:53.56,Default,,0,0,0,,and discovery process while the
Dialogue: 0,0:25:53.56,0:25:54.81,Default,,0,0,0,,app is in the foreground.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:58.47,0:26:01.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Now when the app is suspended,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:01.20,0:26:02.01,Default,,0,0,0,,the peripheral will
Dialogue: 0,0:26:02.01,0:26:03.39,Default,,0,0,0,,automatically be disconnected
Dialogue: 0,0:26:03.39,0:26:04.73,Default,,0,0,0,,and we will not wake up the app
Dialogue: 0,0:26:04.73,0:26:06.20,Default,,0,0,0,,for newly advertised values.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:06.39,0:26:08.39,Default,,0,0,0,,So if you need ongoing updates,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:08.39,0:26:09.16,Default,,0,0,0,,you need to use it in
Dialogue: 0,0:26:09.16,0:26:10.23,Default,,0,0,0,,conjunction with the background
Dialogue: 0,0:26:10.27,0:26:10.49,Default,,0,0,0,,mode.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:11.08,0:26:14.34,Default,,0,0,0,,If you want to learn more, you
Dialogue: 0,0:26:14.34,0:26:15.33,Default,,0,0,0,,should check out the core
Dialogue: 0,0:26:15.33,0:26:16.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Bluetooth session later this
Dialogue: 0,0:26:16.85,0:26:18.95,Default,,0,0,0,,week but first let's take a look
Dialogue: 0,0:26:18.95,0:26:20.33,Default,,0,0,0,,at an example of how an app can
Dialogue: 0,0:26:20.52,0:26:22.15,Default,,0,0,0,,make a use of this.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:23.00,0:26:26.09,Default,,0,0,0,,So ReSound Smart 3D is an app
Dialogue: 0,0:26:26.09,0:26:27.74,Default,,0,0,0,,that lets you connect to
Dialogue: 0,0:26:27.74,0:26:29.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Bluetooth enabled hearing aids
Dialogue: 0,0:26:29.49,0:26:30.89,Default,,0,0,0,,so you can change the listening
Dialogue: 0,0:26:30.89,0:26:32.66,Default,,0,0,0,,environment depending on where
Dialogue: 0,0:26:32.66,0:26:33.13,Default,,0,0,0,,you are.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:33.13,0:26:34.89,Default,,0,0,0,,So I can change from an outdoor
Dialogue: 0,0:26:34.89,0:26:36.05,Default,,0,0,0,,listening environment to a
Dialogue: 0,0:26:36.05,0:26:37.65,Default,,0,0,0,,restaurant, which has a pretty
Dialogue: 0,0:26:37.65,0:26:39.47,Default,,0,0,0,,different audio profile just
Dialogue: 0,0:26:39.47,0:26:40.59,Default,,0,0,0,,with a tap on my wrist.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:40.59,0:26:42.92,Default,,0,0,0,,And with watchOS 4, they can
Dialogue: 0,0:26:42.92,0:26:44.47,Default,,0,0,0,,connect directly to the hearing
Dialogue: 0,0:26:44.47,0:26:46.07,Default,,0,0,0,,aids so that they can make
Dialogue: 0,0:26:46.07,0:26:47.82,Default,,0,0,0,,faster updates and they can
Dialogue: 0,0:26:47.82,0:26:49.59,Default,,0,0,0,,continue using the device when
Dialogue: 0,0:26:49.59,0:26:51.08,Default,,0,0,0,,the phone is no longer present.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:51.79,0:26:52.92,Default,,0,0,0,,And that's core Bluetooth.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:53.52,0:26:58.58,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Applause ]
Dialogue: 0,0:26:59.08,0:27:00.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Now I mentioned before though
Dialogue: 0,0:27:00.07,0:27:01.07,Default,,0,0,0,,there's something called the
Dialogue: 0,0:27:01.16,0:27:02.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Frontmost App State.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:02.36,0:27:03.71,Default,,0,0,0,,This is something that we're
Dialogue: 0,0:27:03.71,0:27:05.23,Default,,0,0,0,,really excited about and I think
Dialogue: 0,0:27:05.23,0:27:06.24,Default,,0,0,0,,it's going to change the way
Dialogue: 0,0:27:06.24,0:27:07.49,Default,,0,0,0,,that we think about creating our
Dialogue: 0,0:27:07.49,0:27:08.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Watch apps.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:09.04,0:27:10.67,Default,,0,0,0,,The experience of using a Watch
Dialogue: 0,0:27:10.67,0:27:12.51,Default,,0,0,0,,app is very different from apps
Dialogue: 0,0:27:12.51,0:27:13.64,Default,,0,0,0,,on other platforms.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:14.24,0:27:15.54,Default,,0,0,0,,When I use an iPhone app, for
Dialogue: 0,0:27:15.54,0:27:17.20,Default,,0,0,0,,example, I open the app.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:17.20,0:27:18.85,Default,,0,0,0,,I use it for some period of time
Dialogue: 0,0:27:19.15,0:27:21.09,Default,,0,0,0,,and eventually I close it by
Dialogue: 0,0:27:21.20,0:27:22.06,Default,,0,0,0,,pressing the home button.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:23.46,0:27:25.65,Default,,0,0,0,,On a Watch app, though, I may
Dialogue: 0,0:27:25.65,0:27:27.23,Default,,0,0,0,,use it for a much shorter period
Dialogue: 0,0:27:27.23,0:27:27.63,Default,,0,0,0,,of time.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:27.94,0:27:30.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Perhaps just a few seconds but I
Dialogue: 0,0:27:30.95,0:27:33.27,Default,,0,0,0,,may use the app dozens or more
Dialogue: 0,0:27:33.27,0:27:35.30,Default,,0,0,0,,time within a single session.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:36.05,0:27:37.89,Default,,0,0,0,,For example, I may use the
Dialogue: 0,0:27:37.89,0:27:39.99,Default,,0,0,0,,reminders app to go shopping at
Dialogue: 0,0:27:39.99,0:27:41.85,Default,,0,0,0,,the grocery store to check off
Dialogue: 0,0:27:41.85,0:27:43.01,Default,,0,0,0,,items as I'm putting them in my
Dialogue: 0,0:27:43.01,0:27:43.32,Default,,0,0,0,,cart.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:44.07,0:27:45.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Every time I put something in my
Dialogue: 0,0:27:45.56,0:27:47.66,Default,,0,0,0,,cart, I raise my wrist and the
Dialogue: 0,0:27:47.66,0:27:49.08,Default,,0,0,0,,app is right there where I left
Dialogue: 0,0:27:49.08,0:27:49.17,Default,,0,0,0,,it.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:49.17,0:27:51.05,Default,,0,0,0,,It makes it really easy for me
Dialogue: 0,0:27:51.05,0:27:52.30,Default,,0,0,0,,to find the item that I'd like
Dialogue: 0,0:27:52.30,0:27:54.89,Default,,0,0,0,,to check off and tap it and then
Dialogue: 0,0:27:54.89,0:27:55.98,Default,,0,0,0,,get on with my shopping.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:57.15,0:27:58.75,Default,,0,0,0,,This period where we resumed to
Dialogue: 0,0:27:58.75,0:28:00.49,Default,,0,0,0,,your app rather than the clock
Dialogue: 0,0:28:00.49,0:28:02.38,Default,,0,0,0,,face is what we call the
Dialogue: 0,0:28:02.38,0:28:04.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Frontmost App State.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:05.10,0:28:06.83,Default,,0,0,0,,In watchOS 3, that period of
Dialogue: 0,0:28:06.83,0:28:08.87,Default,,0,0,0,,time was eight minutes between
Dialogue: 0,0:28:08.87,0:28:09.78,Default,,0,0,0,,each wrist raise.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:10.89,0:28:12.47,Default,,0,0,0,,We found that this was often too
Dialogue: 0,0:28:12.47,0:28:13.85,Default,,0,0,0,,long for users and they would
Dialogue: 0,0:28:13.85,0:28:15.69,Default,,0,0,0,,end up in the same app long
Dialogue: 0,0:28:15.69,0:28:16.88,Default,,0,0,0,,after they were finished using
Dialogue: 0,0:28:17.94,0:28:18.02,Default,,0,0,0,,it.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:18.02,0:28:20.42,Default,,0,0,0,,So in watchOS 3.2, we changed
Dialogue: 0,0:28:20.42,0:28:22.16,Default,,0,0,0,,this limit to two minutes.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:22.70,0:28:26.85,Default,,0,0,0,,And that happens between each
Dialogue: 0,0:28:26.85,0:28:27.48,Default,,0,0,0,,wrist raise.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:27.59,0:28:29.61,Default,,0,0,0,,So for the most part, most
Dialogue: 0,0:28:29.61,0:28:31.89,Default,,0,0,0,,activities will remain frontmost
Dialogue: 0,0:28:31.89,0:28:33.53,Default,,0,0,0,,for the entire duration of using
Dialogue: 0,0:28:34.12,0:28:37.13,Default,,0,0,0,,it but we recognize that there's
Dialogue: 0,0:28:37.13,0:28:38.92,Default,,0,0,0,,some use cases in which you will
Dialogue: 0,0:28:38.92,0:28:40.39,Default,,0,0,0,,need more than two minutes
Dialogue: 0,0:28:40.61,0:28:41.74,Default,,0,0,0,,between each wrist raise.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:41.78,0:28:44.08,Default,,0,0,0,,And for that, we're allowing you
Dialogue: 0,0:28:44.08,0:28:45.67,Default,,0,0,0,,to specify when you need to
Dialogue: 0,0:28:45.67,0:28:46.82,Default,,0,0,0,,extend your frontmost time.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:47.37,0:28:49.92,Default,,0,0,0,,And that will change the time
Dialogue: 0,0:28:49.92,0:28:51.69,Default,,0,0,0,,out back from two minutes out to
Dialogue: 0,0:28:51.69,0:28:52.35,Default,,0,0,0,,eight minutes.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:52.59,0:28:54.18,Default,,0,0,0,,So let's take a look at how you
Dialogue: 0,0:28:54.23,0:28:56.31,Default,,0,0,0,,enable this in code.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:56.52,0:28:57.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Like most of the other things
Dialogue: 0,0:28:57.50,0:28:58.45,Default,,0,0,0,,that we've talked about today,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:58.58,0:28:59.86,Default,,0,0,0,,it's a simple call on the shared
Dialogue: 0,0:28:59.86,0:29:00.39,Default,,0,0,0,,extension.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:00.39,0:29:01.50,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a simple property.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:01.99,0:29:03.33,Default,,0,0,0,,You can set to true whenever you
Dialogue: 0,0:29:03.33,0:29:04.61,Default,,0,0,0,,need to extend your frontmost
Dialogue: 0,0:29:04.61,0:29:04.88,Default,,0,0,0,,time.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:05.72,0:29:09.47,Default,,0,0,0,,You must be judicious about this
Dialogue: 0,0:29:09.47,0:29:11.49,Default,,0,0,0,,though because we don't want
Dialogue: 0,0:29:11.49,0:29:13.58,Default,,0,0,0,,users to remain in apps long
Dialogue: 0,0:29:13.58,0:29:15.16,Default,,0,0,0,,after they're finished using
Dialogue: 0,0:29:15.16,0:29:15.39,Default,,0,0,0,,them.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:15.89,0:29:18.11,Default,,0,0,0,,So let's take a look back at my
Dialogue: 0,0:29:18.11,0:29:19.62,Default,,0,0,0,,reminder shopping list example.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:20.74,0:29:22.90,Default,,0,0,0,,When I turn on -- when I open up
Dialogue: 0,0:29:22.90,0:29:23.96,Default,,0,0,0,,the shopping list, I probably
Dialogue: 0,0:29:23.96,0:29:25.41,Default,,0,0,0,,want to turn on and extended
Dialogue: 0,0:29:25.41,0:29:27.89,Default,,0,0,0,,frontmost time so that if I had
Dialogue: 0,0:29:27.89,0:29:29.93,Default,,0,0,0,,like an item between two aisles
Dialogue: 0,0:29:30.20,0:29:31.10,Default,,0,0,0,,that took longer than two
Dialogue: 0,0:29:31.10,0:29:32.17,Default,,0,0,0,,minutes, I wouldn't have to go
Dialogue: 0,0:29:32.17,0:29:33.56,Default,,0,0,0,,back to open up the app.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:34.67,0:29:36.52,Default,,0,0,0,,But as soon as I've finished the
Dialogue: 0,0:29:36.52,0:29:38.13,Default,,0,0,0,,items in my shopping list, it's
Dialogue: 0,0:29:38.13,0:29:39.39,Default,,0,0,0,,probably a good opportunity to
Dialogue: 0,0:29:39.39,0:29:40.94,Default,,0,0,0,,turn off extended frontmost
Dialogue: 0,0:29:40.94,0:29:41.20,Default,,0,0,0,,time.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:41.38,0:29:42.70,Default,,0,0,0,,So that the app will just
Dialogue: 0,0:29:43.08,0:29:44.20,Default,,0,0,0,,automatically close in the
Dialogue: 0,0:29:44.20,0:29:45.38,Default,,0,0,0,,background without the user
Dialogue: 0,0:29:45.38,0:29:46.49,Default,,0,0,0,,having to do anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:46.96,0:29:48.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Now in addition to giving you
Dialogue: 0,0:29:48.99,0:29:50.88,Default,,0,0,0,,more flexibility for when you
Dialogue: 0,0:29:50.88,0:29:52.59,Default,,0,0,0,,remain in frontmost, we're also
Dialogue: 0,0:29:52.59,0:29:54.32,Default,,0,0,0,,changing some of the behaviors
Dialogue: 0,0:29:54.32,0:29:56.56,Default,,0,0,0,,of the API so that you can have
Dialogue: 0,0:29:56.59,0:29:58.79,Default,,0,0,0,,more up-to-date information and
Dialogue: 0,0:29:58.79,0:30:00.56,Default,,0,0,0,,meet the expectations of users.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:04.07,0:30:05.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Now you can already extend your
Dialogue: 0,0:30:05.41,0:30:07.13,Default,,0,0,0,,run time by up to 30 seconds
Dialogue: 0,0:30:07.61,0:30:10.34,Default,,0,0,0,,using the expiring activity on
Dialogue: 0,0:30:10.40,0:30:11.27,Default,,0,0,0,,NS [phonetic] process info.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:11.46,0:30:13.29,Default,,0,0,0,,And this is a great opportunity
Dialogue: 0,0:30:13.29,0:30:14.56,Default,,0,0,0,,to do things like networking
Dialogue: 0,0:30:14.56,0:30:15.10,Default,,0,0,0,,tasks.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:15.50,0:30:16.95,Default,,0,0,0,,And we've increased the priority
Dialogue: 0,0:30:16.95,0:30:18.62,Default,,0,0,0,,of this request in watchOS 4 so
Dialogue: 0,0:30:18.75,0:30:20.23,Default,,0,0,0,,that you can do more things in
Dialogue: 0,0:30:20.23,0:30:21.30,Default,,0,0,0,,the time that you've requested.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:21.83,0:30:27.13,Default,,0,0,0,,And if Watch connectivity or url
Dialogue: 0,0:30:27.13,0:30:29.20,Default,,0,0,0,,session data comes into your app
Dialogue: 0,0:30:29.54,0:30:30.57,Default,,0,0,0,,while you're in the frontmost
Dialogue: 0,0:30:30.57,0:30:32.15,Default,,0,0,0,,state, we will immediately
Dialogue: 0,0:30:32.15,0:30:34.00,Default,,0,0,0,,resume your app and in most
Dialogue: 0,0:30:34.00,0:30:35.37,Default,,0,0,0,,cases, the payload will begin
Dialogue: 0,0:30:35.37,0:30:37.21,Default,,0,0,0,,downloading immediately as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:38.27,0:30:40.01,Default,,0,0,0,,And if there's important
Dialogue: 0,0:30:40.01,0:30:41.92,Default,,0,0,0,,information that you recognize
Dialogue: 0,0:30:41.92,0:30:43.58,Default,,0,0,0,,in that data, while you're in
Dialogue: 0,0:30:43.58,0:30:44.84,Default,,0,0,0,,the frontmost state if you have
Dialogue: 0,0:30:44.84,0:30:46.96,Default,,0,0,0,,run time, you can play haptics
Dialogue: 0,0:30:47.04,0:30:47.89,Default,,0,0,0,,to alert the user.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:48.42,0:30:51.05,Default,,0,0,0,,And if a notification for your
Dialogue: 0,0:30:51.05,0:30:52.25,Default,,0,0,0,,app comes in while you're in
Dialogue: 0,0:30:52.25,0:30:53.82,Default,,0,0,0,,that state, you could also
Dialogue: 0,0:30:53.82,0:30:54.90,Default,,0,0,0,,handle it using the user
Dialogue: 0,0:30:54.90,0:30:56.73,Default,,0,0,0,,notification API just like you
Dialogue: 0,0:30:56.73,0:30:57.78,Default,,0,0,0,,can when the app is in the
Dialogue: 0,0:30:57.78,0:30:58.29,Default,,0,0,0,,foreground.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:58.84,0:31:01.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's take a look at an example
Dialogue: 0,0:31:01.08,0:31:02.07,Default,,0,0,0,,that ties all of these
Dialogue: 0,0:31:02.07,0:31:03.15,Default,,0,0,0,,capabilities together.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:05.12,0:31:06.86,Default,,0,0,0,,So here we have a simple
Dialogue: 0,0:31:06.86,0:31:08.09,Default,,0,0,0,,ride-sharing app.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:08.33,0:31:09.40,Default,,0,0,0,,It's showing me that I have an
Dialogue: 0,0:31:09.40,0:31:11.72,Default,,0,0,0,,expected five-minute wait time.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:12.58,0:31:14.08,Default,,0,0,0,,This is a great opportunity to
Dialogue: 0,0:31:14.08,0:31:15.83,Default,,0,0,0,,turn extended frontmost time on
Dialogue: 0,0:31:15.90,0:31:17.17,Default,,0,0,0,,because I already know it's
Dialogue: 0,0:31:17.17,0:31:18.39,Default,,0,0,0,,pretty likely that the user's
Dialogue: 0,0:31:18.39,0:31:19.49,Default,,0,0,0,,going to need longer than the
Dialogue: 0,0:31:19.49,0:31:20.44,Default,,0,0,0,,two-minute timeout.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:21.68,0:31:23.06,Default,,0,0,0,,It's going to be a bit of a wait
Dialogue: 0,0:31:23.06,0:31:24.02,Default,,0,0,0,,and I probably don't want to
Dialogue: 0,0:31:24.02,0:31:25.18,Default,,0,0,0,,keep my wrist up the entire
Dialogue: 0,0:31:25.18,0:31:25.55,Default,,0,0,0,,time.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:26.00,0:31:27.88,Default,,0,0,0,,So I tap on the request ride
Dialogue: 0,0:31:27.88,0:31:29.48,Default,,0,0,0,,button and drop my wrist.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:30.08,0:31:32.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Now the screen may be off but
Dialogue: 0,0:31:32.06,0:31:33.55,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm definitely not done using
Dialogue: 0,0:31:33.55,0:31:34.52,Default,,0,0,0,,the app because I'm still
Dialogue: 0,0:31:34.52,0:31:35.33,Default,,0,0,0,,waiting for the ride.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:35.42,0:31:37.52,Default,,0,0,0,,And at some point, the server's
Dialogue: 0,0:31:37.52,0:31:38.39,Default,,0,0,0,,going to send a push
Dialogue: 0,0:31:38.39,0:31:39.74,Default,,0,0,0,,notification that'll get
Dialogue: 0,0:31:39.81,0:31:42.05,Default,,0,0,0,,forwarded to my Watch and at
Dialogue: 0,0:31:42.05,0:31:43.71,Default,,0,0,0,,that point, the app can handle
Dialogue: 0,0:31:43.71,0:31:45.70,Default,,0,0,0,,the notification and recognize
Dialogue: 0,0:31:45.70,0:31:46.97,Default,,0,0,0,,that it's important information
Dialogue: 0,0:31:47.32,0:31:49.15,Default,,0,0,0,,and play a haptic to alert me.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:50.31,0:31:51.60,Default,,0,0,0,,When I raise my wrist, the app
Dialogue: 0,0:31:51.60,0:31:53.61,Default,,0,0,0,,has already been updated showing
Dialogue: 0,0:31:53.61,0:31:55.32,Default,,0,0,0,,me important information like
Dialogue: 0,0:31:55.32,0:31:57.02,Default,,0,0,0,,the arrival time as well as the
Dialogue: 0,0:31:57.02,0:31:59.03,Default,,0,0,0,,driver's name and star rating.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:59.29,0:32:00.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Even the ability to call the
Dialogue: 0,0:32:00.46,0:32:00.89,Default,,0,0,0,,driver.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:01.48,0:32:03.90,Default,,0,0,0,,At this point, I should turn off
Dialogue: 0,0:32:03.90,0:32:05.53,Default,,0,0,0,,extended frontmost time because
Dialogue: 0,0:32:05.53,0:32:06.85,Default,,0,0,0,,it's likely that the user's done
Dialogue: 0,0:32:06.85,0:32:09.13,Default,,0,0,0,,using the app for now, at least.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:09.46,0:32:10.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Getting this frontmost state
Dialogue: 0,0:32:10.74,0:32:12.40,Default,,0,0,0,,right will make your app feel
Dialogue: 0,0:32:12.40,0:32:13.02,Default,,0,0,0,,like magic.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:13.95,0:32:15.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Always knowing when the user's
Dialogue: 0,0:32:15.23,0:32:17.13,Default,,0,0,0,,done using your app as well as
Dialogue: 0,0:32:17.13,0:32:18.86,Default,,0,0,0,,when they need more time in it.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:18.99,0:32:20.65,Default,,0,0,0,,And making sure that the data in
Dialogue: 0,0:32:20.65,0:32:22.40,Default,,0,0,0,,your app is up-to-date and
Dialogue: 0,0:32:22.40,0:32:23.76,Default,,0,0,0,,showing just what the user wants
Dialogue: 0,0:32:23.76,0:32:25.22,Default,,0,0,0,,to see for the next time that
Dialogue: 0,0:32:25.22,0:32:26.20,Default,,0,0,0,,they may use their app.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:26.31,0:32:28.31,Default,,0,0,0,,I'd highly encourage you to
Dialogue: 0,0:32:28.31,0:32:29.70,Default,,0,0,0,,check out the session later
Dialogue: 0,0:32:29.70,0:32:32.32,Default,,0,0,0,,today on the life of a watchOS
Dialogue: 0,0:32:32.65,0:32:32.85,Default,,0,0,0,,app.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:33.08,0:32:34.74,Default,,0,0,0,,This will be going into detail
Dialogue: 0,0:32:34.91,0:32:36.45,Default,,0,0,0,,about app life cycle events,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:36.77,0:32:37.95,Default,,0,0,0,,making use of the frontmost
Dialogue: 0,0:32:37.95,0:32:39.35,Default,,0,0,0,,state as well as background
Dialogue: 0,0:32:39.35,0:32:41.23,Default,,0,0,0,,modes and more to make a great
Dialogue: 0,0:32:41.23,0:32:42.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Watch experience.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:42.73,0:32:46.05,Default,,0,0,0,,To summarize, we've added a
Dialogue: 0,0:32:46.05,0:32:47.74,Default,,0,0,0,,bunch of new capabilities to our
Dialogue: 0,0:32:47.74,0:32:49.57,Default,,0,0,0,,user interface components to
Dialogue: 0,0:32:49.57,0:32:51.19,Default,,0,0,0,,make them flexible, to create
Dialogue: 0,0:32:51.22,0:32:53.18,Default,,0,0,0,,custom user interfaces like
Dialogue: 0,0:32:53.18,0:32:54.19,Default,,0,0,0,,overlapping interface
Dialogue: 0,0:32:54.19,0:32:57.12,Default,,0,0,0,,controllers as well as auto
Dialogue: 0,0:32:57.12,0:32:59.63,Default,,0,0,0,,rotate mode.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:00.37,0:33:01.82,Default,,0,0,0,,We're changing the architecture
Dialogue: 0,0:33:01.82,0:33:03.42,Default,,0,0,0,,of Watch apps to make them
Dialogue: 0,0:33:03.42,0:33:05.10,Default,,0,0,0,,perform even better by loading
Dialogue: 0,0:33:05.10,0:33:06.34,Default,,0,0,0,,the extension and an app into
Dialogue: 0,0:33:06.34,0:33:07.86,Default,,0,0,0,,the same process at run time.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:08.39,0:33:10.67,Default,,0,0,0,,And we're adding new background
Dialogue: 0,0:33:10.67,0:33:12.43,Default,,0,0,0,,modes as well as core Bluetooth
Dialogue: 0,0:33:12.43,0:33:14.28,Default,,0,0,0,,support and the changes that we
Dialogue: 0,0:33:14.28,0:33:15.20,Default,,0,0,0,,just went through for the
Dialogue: 0,0:33:15.20,0:33:16.79,Default,,0,0,0,,frontmost app state, which
Dialogue: 0,0:33:16.79,0:33:18.33,Default,,0,0,0,,should make it easier for you to
Dialogue: 0,0:33:18.33,0:33:19.49,Default,,0,0,0,,keep your app up-to-date for
Dialogue: 0,0:33:19.49,0:33:19.97,Default,,0,0,0,,users.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:20.54,0:33:23.02,Default,,0,0,0,,And I mentioned a number of
Dialogue: 0,0:33:23.02,0:33:23.98,Default,,0,0,0,,sessions that you should check
Dialogue: 0,0:33:23.98,0:33:25.72,Default,,0,0,0,,out this week to learn more
Dialogue: 0,0:33:25.72,0:33:26.80,Default,,0,0,0,,about developing on the Watch
Dialogue: 0,0:33:26.83,0:33:27.32,Default,,0,0,0,,platform.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:28.07,0:33:29.57,Default,,0,0,0,,If you want to get more
Dialogue: 0,0:33:29.57,0:33:31.20,Default,,0,0,0,,information like the session
Dialogue: 0,0:33:31.20,0:33:32.96,Default,,0,0,0,,links for videos as well as
Dialogue: 0,0:33:32.96,0:33:34.68,Default,,0,0,0,,other resources, please visit
Dialogue: 0,0:33:34.68,0:33:36.19,Default,,0,0,0,,the developer.apple.com link.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:36.74,0:33:38.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you so much for coming to
Dialogue: 0,0:33:38.17,0:33:39.54,Default,,0,0,0,,hear what's new in watchOS 4.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:39.54,0:33:40.35,Default,,0,0,0,,I can't wait to see what you
Dialogue: 0,0:33:40.35,0:33:40.98,Default,,0,0,0,,guys build next.
